### AidFlow API — Allocations endpoints
# REST Client extension: click 'Send Request' above each block

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000/api/v1
@token = REPLACE_WITH_JWT_TOKEN

### List allocations (501 in Sprint 1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/allocations
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get allocation by ID (501 in Sprint 1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/allocations/ALLOCATION_ID
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Create allocation (501 in Sprint 1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/allocations
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "programId": "PROGRAM_ID",
  "beneficiaryId": "BENEFICIARY_ID",
  "amount": 200,
  "currency": "USD",
  "note": "Monthly food allowance"
}

### Approve allocation (501 in Sprint 1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/allocations/ALLOCATION_ID/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Reject allocation (501 in Sprint 1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/allocations/ALLOCATION_ID/reject
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "reason": "Duplicate entry"
}
